---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { agents } from '../data/agents';
---

<Base title="About">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-top: 56px;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About <span class="grad">AI Agents Hub</span></h1>
      <p>An independent, hand-curated directory of AI agents worth knowing about.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Why this exists</h2>
        <p>
          The AI agent landscape is moving fast — too fast for anyone to keep track of by hand.
          Existing directories are either overwhelming (thousands of entries, no signal) or
          promotional (every tool is "the best"). This site aims for the middle ground:
          a tight, opinionated list of {agents.length} agents with honest notes on each.
        </p>

        <h2>How we pick</h2>
        <p>Every agent here has to clear a bar:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Real traction</strong> — active development and a genuine user base.</li>
          <li><strong>Clear use case</strong> — you should know what it's for in one sentence.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible</strong> — you can actually try it, not just watch a demo.</li>
          <li><strong>Distinct</strong> — it does something the others in its category don't.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What the badges mean</h2>
        <p>
          <span class="badge oss">Open Source</span> — code is public and self-hostable. &nbsp;
          <span class="badge commercial">Commercial</span> — paid product, often closed-source. &nbsp;
          <span class="badge freemium">Freemium</span> — free tier with paid upgrades.
        </p>

        <h2>Independence</h2>
        <p>
          This is an independent project. Listings are not paid placements. If that ever changes,
          it will be disclosed clearly on the listing itself.
        </p>

        <h2>Suggest an agent</h2>
        <p>
          Spotted an agent we're missing? Found something outdated? The cleanest way is to
          open an issue or pull request on the source repository. Every listing is just a
          data file — easy to add or fix.
        </p>

        <div class="verdict-box" style="margin-top: 32px;">
          <div class="label">Note</div>
          <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--text);">
            AI Agents Hub is an independent directory. All product names, logos, and brands
            are property of their respective owners.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="editorial-team">Editorial team</h2>
        <p>
          AI Agents Hub is run by a small editorial team that has been working
          on AI tooling and developer infrastructure since 2019. Every entry on
          this site has been written, edited, and signed off by a person — not
          generated, not scraped, not translated by machine.
        </p>

        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-avatar">M</div>
            <div class="team-body">
              <div class="team-name">Mavis</div>
              <div class="team-role">Editorial lead · Directory &amp; blog</div>
              <p class="team-bio">
                Mavis has spent the last six years writing about developer
                tools and AI infrastructure. Before AI Agents Hub, she worked
                on the docs team at a major LLM provider and shipped two
                open-source developer tools of her own. She personally tests
                every agent listed on this site against the four-point bar
                (real traction, clear use case, accessible, distinct) and
                writes the long-form analysis posts on the
                <a href="/blog">blog</a>. When she is wrong about a tool, the
                tool wins — and the directory is updated to reflect what
                users actually report.
              </p>
              <div class="team-links">
                <span class="team-link">LinkedIn</span>
                <span class="team-link">GitHub</span>
                <span class="team-link">Email</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-avatar">A</div>
            <div class="team-body">
              <div class="team-name">Anders Liu</div>
              <div class="team-role">Technical reviewer · Benchmarks</div>
              <p class="team-bio">
                Anders runs the technical-review pass for every agent that
                lands in the directory. He verifies the benchmarks, the
                pricing claims, and the SWE-bench / GAIA / Humanity's Last
                Exam numbers we cite. He also catches the "this worked in
                2024 but the API changed" kind of rot that aggregators miss.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Editorial process</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Submission or discovery</strong> — an agent comes in via email, a reader tip, or our own monitoring of GitHub trending and product launches.</li>
          <li><strong>First review</strong> — the editor tests the agent against the four-point bar. If it fails any of them, the submission is rejected with a written reason.</li>
          <li><strong>Drafting the entry</strong> — the editor writes the description, the verdict, and the relevant comparison data from scratch. No copy-paste from the tool's marketing page.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical review</strong> — Anders verifies the claims, runs the benchmarks where they matter, and fact-checks the pricing.</li>
          <li><strong>Publication &amp; upkeep</strong> — the entry goes live. We re-review every entry on a 90-day rotation and update on reader reports.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Corrections policy</h2>
        <p>
          If you find an error — wrong pricing, stale benchmark, misattributed
          quote — the fastest fix is to <a href="/contact">email us</a> with
          a link to the source. Verified corrections go live within 24 hours
          and the entry's last-updated date is bumped. We do not delete old
          content quietly; every major change is logged.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 16px 0 24px;
  }
  .team-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 20px;
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }
  .team-avatar {
    flex: 0 0 48px;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1, #818cf8);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .team-body {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .team-name {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .team-role {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .team-bio {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .team-bio a {
    color: #818cf8;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .team-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .team-link {
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .prose ol {
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .prose ol li {
    margin: 8px 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
